    <bodyBottom>
      <Value><![CDATA[<p><strong>What makes our courses different?</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Small class numbers – eight maximum – ensuring you get personal attention</li>
<li>We place a huge amount of emphasis on the practical element of this course …working within a gym is crucial and no amount of home-study can replace this.</li>
<li>Access to your tutor between units/weekends via email</li>
<li>Fun, enjoyable approach to learning whether or not you are accustomed to studying</li>
<li>Face to face learning with encouragement and feedback helps you to learn more quickly</li>
<li>We have a reputation for bringing theory to life</li>
<li>Working with the same group of students for the duration of your course, helps build confidence</li>
<li>We know our stuff! All of our tutors have extensive experience of training clients, Indoor Cycling, Circuits and Personal Training.</li>
</ul>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Courses run regularly throughout the year. For further details and course dates, please email </strong><a href="mailto:sportsreception@qmu.ac.uk"><strong>sportsreception@qmu.ac.uk</strong></a></p>]]></Value>
    </bodyBottom>
